# Experience Index

> Read this index before analysis, design, implementation, self-check, and before each stage begins a concrete task.
> Keep it lightweight. Store only keywords, file paths, load timing, and confidence.

## How To Use

1. Match the request against the keywords below
2. Load only matching experience files
3. Check the current change `session-memory.md` for candidate lessons
4. `high` confidence entries must be followed
5. Promote new lessons only after validation
6. After each stage-level task completes, review new lessons and decide whether they belong in `session-memory.md`, an experience file, or a formal rule

## Experience Map

| Keywords | Experience File | When To Load | Confidence | Notes |
|----------|-----------------|--------------|------------|-------|
| architecture, design | experience/architecture/common-errors.md | before design | low | Review common mistakes before locking the design. |
| review, self-check | experience/review/self-check.md | before completion | low | Use targeted self-check before finishing work. |

## Confidence Levels

- `low`: newly captured lesson
- `medium`: validated more than once
- `high`: repeatedly validated or high-risk rule

Mature experience that is directly relevant to the current task should not only be loaded. It should be actively fused into the current requirement, change, plan, or execution approach.
